    "description": "<p>Elcome, founded in 1970, is one of the largest marine technology system integrators in the world. With offices from Spain to Singapore, Elcome is firmly positioned to provide world-class support for your fleet.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Elcome’s factory trained engineers visit more than 800 ships every month worldwide with an impressive first-time fix-rate of 96 percent and is supported by shore-based network of 23 business centers located in 12 countries from Strait of Gibraltar to Straits of Malacca.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>The Elcome Group employs a workforce of over 500 people, 40 percent of which are factory-trained engineers and technicians. Areas of specialization include navigation, communication, automation, homeland security, satellite airtime and connectivity services, nautical charts &amp; publications, safety, electricals, training, shipboard service, and lifecycle extension support.</p>",
